<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38163d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38163d">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38163d"> 163(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Shesmu = / headsman</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Judgment of Osiris took place near Abydos, probably at midnight, and a decree of swift annihilation was passed by him on the damned. Their heads were cut off by the <mark>headsman</mark> of Osiris, who was called <mark>Shesmu</mark> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> and their bodies dismembered and destroyed in pits of fire. There was no eternal punishment for men, for the wicked were annihilated quickly and completely; but inasmuch as Osiris sat in judgment and doomed the wicked to destruction daily, the infliction of punishment never ceased. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a> (1920) 21</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
